deleverageAccount(address,address,addres.notice: If an account is below the minimum collateral ratio, this method wil deleverage (liquidate) that account. `depositAmountPrimeCash` in the borrow currency will be transferred from the liquidator and used to offset the account's debt position. The liquidator will receive either vaultShares or cash depending.

params.account: the address that will exit the vault
params.currencyIndex: 0 refers to primary borrow, 1 or 2 will refer to one of the secondary currencies (if any)
params.depositUnderlyingInternal: amount of underlying to deposit, in 8 decimal underlying precision
params.liquidator: the address that will receive profits from liquidation

returns.depositAmountPrimeCash: amount of prime cash deposited from liquidation
returns.vaultSharesToLiquidator: amount of vaultShares received from liquidation
